rComments: i wrote the very first review of this prof after i wrote the midterm. quick update after the final: - term paper graded very generously -final exam much, much easier than the midterm -textbook less important, but still important. -final class average around B+ despite the scare on the 1st midterm however, still as monotone and as boring as ever...
As long as you attend for quizzes, you'll get an extra 10%. I studied the quiz questions and some notes and ended up with a 99 on the final. Def take her if looking to bring up your average.
The midterm was a little tough if you didn't read the textbook or barely studied but the final and the paper were both graded very easily. Don't go to lectures they are pointless.

Lectures are completely useless, no point in attending them because she reads from her slides. Read through Linden's book at least once and no need to take notes (waste of time) just try to understand what your reading and personally I always did the reading shortly before the exam. Take notes on Grossman's book (it's super short simple and easy).

do your notes based off of the textbook and really understand the stuff she emphasizes in her slides. memorize the textbook, and midterm and exam are sups easy. not a good lecturer but offers good help. offers extra credit option on exam which is def a boost. class can be boring af but tis an noice A in the end

The prof is very monotone, she does not make the class interesting but it's an easy A. The class course consisted of 10 in class quizzes which only counts as participation, 1 midterm, 1 essay and the final exam. Don't bother purchasing the textbook. Just memorize the in class quizzes for the midterm& final exam and congrats, you just passed.

1st midterm avg in the low 60s. was very misleading in telling us how to study. little taken from the lectures/slides. everything from the textbook. don't listen to a word she says when explaining how to study for the midterm. just read the textbook. she's a bland, monotone, unfunny, uninteresting lecturer shes always willing to help though...
